  number =	 3,
  pages =	 "297-310",
  abstract =	 "The determination of contract wages in West Germany is
		  studied within a bargaining framework, taking into
		  account some institutional features of the bargaining
		  system as well as the influence of economic forecasts and
		  wage concepts. Cointegration regressions suggest that in
		  the long run nominal contract wages are linked to prices
