  type =	 "Discussion Paper",
  number =	 801,
  month =	 jul,
  abstract=	 "This paper investigates economic determinants and
		  effects of aggregate union membership in the Federal
		  Republic of  Germany. We establish that in the long run,
		  high union  membership levels coincide not only with a
		  large labour force,  but also with a high level of real
