  number =	 5829,
  abstract =	 "Using data from the German Socio Economic Panel, I
		  describe the incidence, attributes, and outcomes of
		  conitnuous training received by workers in Germany
		  between 1986 and 1989. Further training is primarily a
		  white collar phenomenon and is concentrated among the
		  more highly educated, and in the service sector and in
		  public administration. Much of this training seems to be
